hypoglycemia i thought chromium would be beneficial but taking chromium picolinate tablet a day seems to make it worse is that possible or am i imagining things chromium picolinate is a potentiator of insulin which means that it helps insulin move sugar out of the bloodstream and into the body's cells this can increase any hypoglycemic tendencies that you may have talk to your doctor about this by the way many chromium supplements have somewhere on the label a warning that they may reduce blood sugar hope this helps Hypoglycemia Diabetes mellitus Insulin resistance Nutrition Polycystic ovary syndrome Blood sugar Hyperglycemia Hyperinsulinemic hypoglycemia Anti-diabetic drug Hormone replacement therapy (trans) Sulfonylurea Glucokinase Atherosclerosis Clinical depression Diabetic ketoacidosis Stroke Panic attack Dietary fiber Glycogen Prostate cancer Alzheimer's disease Bodybuilding Fructose Intensive insulinotherapy Glucose meter Tocopherol Gastroparesis Epinephrine Congenital hyperinsulinism Knife Stomach cancer Paracetamol Diabetic nephropathy Cancer Iron Folic acid Atkins Nutritional Approach Antiretroviral drug Insulinoma Alcoholism Blood Aspirin Crohn's disease Post-traumatic stress disorder Milk Low-carbohydrate diet Hyperkalemia Growth hormone treatment Senescence Growth hormone deficiency LSD Psoriasis Metastasis Endocrinology Experimental cancer treatment Diabetic hypoglycemia Chlorophyta Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Growth hormone Protein-energy malnutrition First aid Cannabis (drug) Chronic fatigue syndrome Whipple's triad Garlic Chromium Attention-deficit hyperactivity disorder Glycemia Protein Altruism Signal transduction Multiple sclerosis Calorie restriction Red blood cell Corrosion Dieting Breastfeeding Sleep Dehydroepiandrosterone Migraine Homeostasis Glucagon Glucose tolerance test Cortisol Exercise Psychosis Biotin Colorectal cancer Adiponectin Hormone Memento (film) Bipolar disorder Glycation Herpes simplex virus Gene therapy Functional magnetic resonan